## 🏗️ Architecture Comparison

| Aspect | IPv4 | IPv6 |
|---|---|---|
| Address space | 32-bit (~4.3B) | 128-bit (2¹²⁸) |
| Notation | Dotted-decimal | Hex + colons |
| Header | Variable length (options field) | Fixed length + extension headers |
| Address resolution | ARP | NDP (Neighbor Discovery Protocol) |
| Autoconfig | DHCP (dynamic) or manual | SLAAC (stateless) or DHCPv6 |
| NAT | Essential (address conservation) | Not required |
| Security | IPsec optional | IPsec mandatory/native |
| Fragmentation | Routers can fragment packets (overhead + security concern) | Handled differently, less overhead |

### Hierarchical Allocation (both protocols)
```
IANA → Regional Internet Registries (RIRs: ARIN, RIPE NCC, etc.)
     → Local Internet Registries / ISPs
     → End-users
```
- IPv6: ISPs typically hand end-users **/48 or /56** prefixes — generous room to subnet internally.

