## 🛡️ Defensive Engineering Notes

| Concept | Defensive Action |
|---|---|
| Network segmentation | Subnet/VLAN by security zone (servers, workstations, IoT, guest Wi-Fi) + ACLs between segments to limit lateral movement |
| Private IP space | Keep internal systems on private ranges; audit NAT config regularly to prevent accidental exposure |
| IP inventory | Use IPAM; scan for rogue/unexpected IPs; enforce assignment/reclamation policy |
| IPv6-specific | Disable IPv6 if unused (reduces attack surface); secure SLAAC (watch for rogue routers advertising bad prefixes); firewall ICMPv6 properly (different from ICMPv4); enforce IPsec policy if in use |
| IDS/IPS | Monitor both IPv4 and IPv6 traffic at perimeter and inter-zone points |
| Rate limiting | Limit connection/packet rates per IP/subnet to blunt DoS attempts |

